INSERT INTO `home_page_key_offering` (`id`, `name`, `body`, `slug`, `bgi`, `bgit`) VALUES
(1, 'BUSINESS TRANSACTION RESTRUCTURING', '<p>Periodical review of the business structure and transaction is one of the pre requisite to remain in competition. We assist our clients on the business/ transaction restructuring which are the most tax efficient as per the present tax laws. Under this service line, we also undertake the health check from tax perspective and suggest the areas of future tax exposure and tax saving opportunities.</p>\r\n<p>Comprehensive assessment of the possible legal risks related to the corporate status, assets, contracts, securities, intellectual property etc. of the target company concerned is required for investment, mergers and Acquisition.</p>\r\n<p>The ideal structuring of the transaction is a composition of financial, tax and legal matters. The drafting/vetting of the transaction contracts and agreements cannot be done without the special attention from a business-minded lawyer. We have a team of specialised team of lawyer for your requirement.</p>\r\n<h3>How Taxpert Professionals can assist you:</h3>\r\n<p>Assistance in the drafting the letter of intent/confidentiality and exclusivity agreements/the share purchase agreement (SPA)/the representations and warranties, etc.</p>\r\n<p>Assistance in complete legal due diligence resulting in an assessment of the potential exposures and provide potential solutions that mitigate the potential exposures.</p>\r\n<p>Advisory services on the legal aspects of the deal structuring and its legal implementation;</p>\r\n<p>Assistance in closing of the deal and advise during the post-deal phase (e.g. advise on enforcement of indemnities for breach of representations and warranties or price adjustment mechanisms; action aimed at minimizing or curtailing the tax, legal, labour or other risks detected in the due diligence/health check.</p>', 'business-transaction-restructuring', 'Li_ght_ho_use2.jpg', 'sasasasa'),
(2, 'COMPANY INCORPORATION AND FORMATION', '<h3>PROCESS OF INCORPORATION OF PRIVATE LIMITED COMPANY</h3>\r\n<h3>STAGE I:</h3>\r\n<p>Directors Identification Number (DIN) &amp; Digital Signatures Certificates (DSC)</p>\r\n<p>Directors Identification Number (&lsquo;DIN&rsquo;) is the unique number required for appointment as a director in a company. The applicant needs to apply with the address and identity proof. The application need to be certified by the qualified Chartered Accountant/ Company Secretary;</p>\r\n<p>For Private Limited minimum number of directors required is 2 (TWO)</p>\r\n<p>The process of company incorporation is now online and company is incorporated through MCA21 of the Ministry of Company Affairs. For signing the documents, DSC is required. Any one proposed director may apply for DSC;</p>\r\n<p>Estimated Time Involved: - Seven Working Days after receiving all the required documents</p>\r\n<h3>STAGE II:</h3>\r\n<p>Name Approval of the Company</p>\r\n<p>After DIN and DSC, name of the company can be applied. The name should contain the proposed name and the activity of the company. Generally three proposed names need to be files;</p>\r\n<p>Application for name approval shall be filed in FORM A1 and shall be digitally signed by the proposed director and by a qualified chartered accountant</p>\r\n<p>Estimated Time Involved: - one week [after receiving DIN/DSC];</p>\r\n<h3>STAGE III:</h3>\r\n<p>Drafting of Legal Documents/Incorporation of Company</p>\r\n<p>The third step includes the following process</p>\r\n<p>Drafting of Memorandum and Articles of Association; The Memorandum contains the main objects and other objects of the company. The Article of the company contains the by-laws of the company. These two documents are the basic documents of the company.</p>\r\n<p>Printing of Memorandum and Articles of Association and getting it stamped; the Stamp duty depends on the paid up capital of the company</p>\r\n<p>Filing of Various forms : Form 18/ Form 32/ Form 1</p>\r\n<p>Preparation of documents (like Power of Attorney etc) prescribed under the Companies Act for incorporation of a company; and</p>\r\n<p>Getting the documents pre-scrutinized</p>\r\n<p>Filing of documents with the ROC</p>\r\n<p>Liaising with the ROC and</p>\r\n<p>Obtaining Certificate of Incorporation</p>\r\n<p>Estimated Time Involved: The time taken by Registrar of Companies in giving the approval varies from 7-10days usually</p>', 'company-incorporation-and-formation', '', 'jj'),
(3, 'NGO TRUST FORMATION', '<h3>PROCESS OF FORMATION OF TRUST</h3>\r\n<h3>Formation of Charitable Trust</h3>\r\n<p>A charitable organization is ordinarily formed by way of the trust, or a company limited by guarantee under section 25 of the Companies Act, 1956 or a society under the Societies Registration Act, 1986. A trust can be oral but for recognition as a charitable institution, it should be in writing and conform to the provisions of the Indian Trust Act, 1882. A valid Trust has to have three certainties:</p>\r\n<p>a. Property</p>\r\n<p>b. Objects</p>\r\n<p>c. Beneficiaries</p>\r\n<p>A trust could be private trust or a public trust depending upon the beneficiaries, whether specified individuals or general public</p>\r\n<p>The trust should have at least two trustees for formation of a trust;</p>\r\n<p>The corpus of the trust should be identified;</p>\r\n<p>Drafting of trust deed</p>', 'ngo-trust-formation', '', ''),
(4, 'DRAFTING AND VETTING OF AGREMENTS', '<p>Agreement entered between two entities may have serious tax and business implications which may be mitigated by proper and lawful tax planning.  Further, issues like associate enterprise, nature of service, bifurcation of consideration are also few issues which need careful tax considerations. We provide the services in relation to vetting of agreement, contract for the purpose of tax implications/tax efficiencies.</p>', 'drafting-and-vetting-of-agrements', '', ''),
(5, 'SPECIAL ECONOMIC ZONE / EOU', '<p>SEZ is a specifically delineated duty free enclave deemed to be a foreign territory for purpose of trade operations and tariffs. Comprehensive legislation i.e. the Special Economic Zone Act, 2005 and the Special Economic Zone Rules, 2006 have been introduced for proper functioning of the scheme. The aim is also to popularize SEZs amongst private investors. Accordingly legislation framework for the SEZ Scheme is as under:</p>\r\n<p>The SEZ Act contains provisions for establishment, development and management of SEZ for the promotion of exports and related matters.</p>\r\n<p>The SEZ Rules provides guidelines and procedures for effective implementation/ operation of the SEZ Act;</p>\r\n<p>The State SEZ Policy, which prescribes guidelines and various policies for giving effect to the SEZ Act and provides for substantive and procedural benefits offered by the State to SEZ developers and the Units within the State;</p>\r\n<p>The SEZ Scheme has been introduced to encourage investment, bringing about increase in employment opportunities, promotion of exports of goods and services, development of infrastructure facilities, technical knowledge. In order to meet these objectives significant tax concessions have been offered to SEZ developer and the Units in SEZ</p>', 'special-economic-zone-eou', '', ''),
(6, 'DUE DILIGIENCE', '<p>We undertake the Due Diligence and health check in various segments like Foreign exchange management Act, Companies Act, Income Tax Act to identify the future exposure / tax opportunities of the target business entity. The purpose of Due Diligence/health Check may be for merger, acquisition or joint venture.</p>', 'due-diligience', '', ''),
(7, 'IE CODE', '<h3>PROCESS FOR IMPORTER & EXPORTER CODE:</h3>\r\n<div>Section 7 of the Foreign Trade (Development and Regulation) Act, 1992, no person shall make any import or export except under an Importer-Exporter Code Number granted by the Director General or the officer authorised by the Director General in this behalf, in accordance with the procedure specified in this behalf by the Director General.Guidelines/</div>\r\n<h3>Documents required for applying for new IEC number:</h3>\r\n<h3>Application must be accompanied by documents as per details given below:</h3>\r\n<div>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Demand Draft of Rs.250/- evidencing payment of application fee in favor of the concerned regional office of DGFT.</li>\r\n<li>Certificate from the Banker of the applicant firm in the specified format. (Please ensure that code of the authorized signatory of the bank should be mentioned on the certificate).</li>\r\n<li>Self certified copy of Permanent Account Number (PAN) of the proprietor ship firm/company issued by Income Tax Authorities.</li>\r\n<li>Self certified copy of Permanent Account Number (PAN) of the applicant issued by Income Tax Authorities. (In case of Proprietorship Firm PAN shall be the same).</li>\r\n<li>Two copies of passport size photographs of the applicant</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>', 'ie-code', '', ''),
(8, 'ON GOING TAX COMPLIANCE', '<p>Indirect Tax is the predominant form of consumption tax system in India. On average it takes longer to comply with VAT around the world, than to comply with corporate income tax.</p>\r\n<p>The time needed to comply with Tax varies considerably and depends on various factors like the typr of business entity, qualification of staff members and tax policies. Tax compliance tends to be more time-consuming in Indian because it is administered by the different tax authority that deals with service tax, VAT, Central Excise separately. In case of VAT/ Octroi / Entry Tax administrative procedures vary from State to State and these have a significant impact on how long it takes to comply with VAT/Octroi/ Entry Tax?</p>\r\n<p>Compliance takes longer where extra documentation has to be submitted with the return. There is a correlation between the Tax compliance burden and the time delay in receiving a VAT refund. Typically, where it takes longer to receive a refund, it takes longer to comply.</p>\r\n<p>Compliance is one of the important function of the organization however, it involves huge cost as well require up-to-date knowledge.  A nominal non compliance of the tax laws may cost very high. We provide professional services in relation to the day to day compliance of the organization.</p>', 'on-going-tax-compliance', '', ''),
(9, 'Quick Link', '<p>sdfsdfsdfhh</p>', 'quick-link', '', 'dsdfdsf'),
(10, 'Dinesh', '<p>sdsdddddddddddddddddddddd</p>', 'dinesh', '', 'sdsdsds');

